82add020-0140-4e7e-b71f-3ede5e749ff4.10ca0d42-198b-421a-8910-3ae02b9dbeb4.description=
Computes a mathematical operation.

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the first value
value2 - the second value
operator - operation to perform (+,-,*,/,%);

Responses\:
success - the expression was evaluated.
failure - the expression could not be evaluated.

Returns\: the value of the expression.

82add020-0140-4e7e-b71f-3ede5e749ff4.description=
Checks for any filesystem errors.
Works on W2K and earlier versions of Windows.

inputs\:
diagnostic so far - used to chain diagnostics together, and get one report. The output of previous diagnostics, or blank.
freespace threshold - minimum acceptable % freespace as a decimal.
host - host to check.
user - username to login to host with.
password - password for user.

Responses\:
success - Diagnostic successful.
failure - something went wrong.
82add020-0140-4e7e-b71f-3ede5e749ff4.e3fb673c-dcd4-437f-a425-8693119aef3d.transition.description=${name} has maximum capacity of ${size}.
flow.name: Filesystem Diagnostic W2K and Before

staticBinding.value: Select Name, FreeSpace, Size from Win32_LogicalDisk where DriveType = 3
Ensure ${name} is online and functional. The most likely cause of this problem is if the drive is reporting a total capacity of 0 bytes.
